cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DB, cs.CR

This paper discusses various XML-based approaches for representing digital assets, which are relevant to the digital library community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also mentions the use of the MPEG-21 Digital Item Declaration in a repository environment, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses the representation of multimedia content, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper briefly touches on the potential relevance of MPEG-21 DID to digital rights management, which could classify it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
